    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2005-09-08</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2005-09-20T18:44:02Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>First Responders Interoperable Communications Act of 2005 - Authorizes the Secretary of Homeland Security to make grants, on a competitive basis, to states, local governments, local law enforcement agencies, and local fire departments to assist in: (1) improving communication systems to allow for real-time, interoperable communication between state and local first responders; or (2) the purchase of communication systems that allow for such communication.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
